#######
# 5: Mouse and Key bindings
#
# Contexts:
#     R = Root Window                 rrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrr
#     W = Application Window          rIrrrr<---------^rrrrr
#     F = Frame Corners               rrrrrr[13TTTT642]rrrrr
#     S = Frame Sides                 rIrrrr[wwwwwwwww]rrrrr
#     T = Title Bar                   rrrrrr[wwwwwwwww]rrrrr
#     I = Icon                        rIrrrrv_________>rrrrr
#                                     rrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrr
#
#     Numbers are buttons: [1 3 5 7 9  TTTTT  0 8 6 4 2]
#
# Modifiers: (A)ny, (C)ontrol, (S)hift, (M)eta, (N)othing
#
# Format: Key <X>  <Context> <Modifier> <Action>
#         Mouse <X> <Context> <Modifier> <Action>
####################

# Alt-F1 or Menu to load the root menu and Alt-Tab for a WindowList.
# Ctrl-F1/F2/F3/F4 will switch between the Virtual Desktops.
# Super_R (windows key) will launch a terminal.
#
# Silent supresses any errors (such as keyboards with no Menu key).
Silent Key F1 A M Menu MenuFvwmRoot
#Silent Key Menu A A Menu MenuFvwmRoot

# Silent Key XF86RotateWindows A N Exec exec /home/user/bin/rotate-cycle normal
Silent Key Page_Up A CM Exec exec /home/wyatt/bin/volup
Silent Key Page_Down A CM Exec exec /home/wyatt/bin/voldown
Silent Key KP_Page_Up A CM Exec exec /home/wyatt/bin/volup
Silent Key KP_Page_Down A CM Exec exec /home/wyatt/bin/voldown
Silent Key KP_9 A CM Exec exec /home/wyatt/bin/volup
Silent Key KP_3 A CM Exec exec /home/wyatt/bin/voldown
# Silent Key XF86TaskPane A N Exec exec /home/user/bin/rotate-cycle invert

# Menu key is compose key

# F13, sent from xdotool as a hack/workaround since fvwmcommand is gone now
# in fvwm3
Silent Key 3270_FieldMark A N WindowList Root c c CurrentDesk

#Silent Key Tab A M WindowList Root c c NoDeskSort, SelectOnRelease Meta_L
#Silent Key Tab A M WindowList Root c c NoDeskSort, IconifiedAtEnd, SelectOnRelease Meta_L
#Silent Key Tab A M WindowList Root c c IconifiedAtEnd, CurrentDesk, SelectOnRelease Meta_L
Silent Key Tab A M WindowList Root c c CurrentDesk, SelectOnRelease Meta_L
# For fvwm3, since fvwmcommand doesn't work anymore.
# Made my applet send alt+shift+tab as well.
# Silent Key Tab A SM WindowList Root c c CurrentDesk, SelectOnRelease
# Edit: FVWM3 release 1.0.0 has FvwmPrompt; problem solved.
#Silent Key F1 A C GotoDesk 0 0
#Silent Key F2 A C GotoDesk 0 1
#Silent Key F3 A C GotoDesk 0 2
#Silent Key F4 A C GotoDesk 0 3
Silent Key F13 A A 
# Silent Key Super_R A A Exec exec mate-terminal

# ctrl+alt+arrowkey to cycle through desks
# replace 'C' with 'A' (anything) to make it "alt+arrowkey" instead
Silent Key Left A CM GotoDesk  -1 0 0 3
Silent Key KP_Left A CM GotoDesk  -1 0 0 3
Silent Key Right A CM GotoDesk +1 0 0 3
Silent Key KP_Right A CM GotoDesk +1 0 0 3
# ctrl+shift+leftArrow or ctrl+shift+rightArrow to rotate
#Silent Key Right A CS Exec exec $HOME/bin/rotate-left
#Silent Key Left A CS Exec exec $HOME/bin/rotate-normal
# ctrl+alt+upArrow to bump brightness up
Silent Key Up A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightup_acpi
Silent Key KP_Up A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightup_acpi
# ctrl+alt+downArrow to bump brightness down
Silent Key Down A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightdown_acpi
Silent Key KP_Down A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightdown_acpi
# ctrl+super+up and ctrl+super+down
Silent Key Up A C4 Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightup_acpi
Silent Key Down A C4 Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightdown_acpi
Silent Key KP_Up A C4 Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightup_acpi
Silent Key KP_Down A C4 Exec exec $HOME/bin/brightdown_acpi

# u2412m external brightness up/down on ctrl+alt+I and ctrl+alt+K
Silent Key 'i' A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/u2412m_brightup
Silent Key 'k' A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/u2412m_brightdown

# toggle LCD
Silent Key XF86Launch1 A S Exec exec $HOME/bin/toggle-lcd

# lcdoff
Silent Key XF86Launch1 A C Exec exec $HOME/bin/lcdoff

Silent Key XF86Launch1 A M Exec exec $HOME/bin/lcdon

# fullscreen - hide window borders, hide title bar, and then maximize.
# the same shortcut 'un-toggles' it.
# ctrl-alt-g
#Silent Key g A CM FullScreenMax
# ctrl-alt-8
Silent Key 8 A CM FullScreenMaxHandler

Silent Key 2 A CM Exec exec halfWindowSize
Silent Key 4 A CM Exec exec doubleWindowSize
Silent Key 3 A CM Exec exec window.3x
Silent Key 5 A CM Exec exec window3x

# hide window (with my special script which uses xdotool)
# ctrl-alt-h
Silent Key h A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/hidewindow.sh

# restart fvwm
# ctrl-alt-r
Silent Key r A CM Restart

# show last hidden window (with my special script)
# 'u' for 'unhide'
# ctrl-alt-u
Silent Key u A CM Exec exec $HOME/bin/showwindow.sh

# toggle borders
# ctrl-alt-b
Silent Key b A CM ToggleBorders

DestroyFunc WineMaximizeHack
AddToFunc WineMaximizeHack
+ I Current (Maximized) WindowStyle Borders
+ I TestRc (NoMatch) WindowStyle !Borders
+ I UpdateStyles
+ I RefreshWindow
+ I Maximize ewmhiwa growonwindowlayer
+ I RefreshWindow
+ I Maximize forget

